<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Madeleine Albright Arrives in Zagreb for Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501113094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1100 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Announcer] American Ambassador to the United Nations 
Madeleine Albright has arrived in Zagreb. Tihomir Vinkovic 
reports for Croatian Radio: 
  [Vinkovic] Upon arrival at Zagreb aiport Ambassador Albright 
told journalists there were three reasons for her visit to 
Croatia: First is the stand of the American Administration that 
there is no justification of aggression, war crimes, and 
thwarting dispatch of humanitarian aid. The American 
Administration supports the sovereignty and the territorial 
integrity of the Republic of Croatia. Currently occupied 
Croatian territories have to be returned in a peaceful way and 
through a political solution, ambassador Albright said. The 
U.S. Government will support efforts for the restoration of 
peace and dispatch of humanitarian aid, particularly in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  In the course of her visit to Croatia Ambassador Albright is 
to meet President Tudjman, Croatian Foreign Minister Mate 
Granic, representatives of the UN Protection Forces, UN High 
Commissioner for Refugees, and other humanitarian organizations. 

</TEXT>

