<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HVO, Croatian Army Shell Mostar `Fiercely' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0401195594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0401195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 4th Corps press center] </F>
  [Text] Today, at around 1200 the troops of the Croatian 
Defense Council [HVO] and the Croatian Army directed fierce 
mortar fire at the central parts of the city and the Mostar 
district of Madoljice. Three people were seriously injured as a 
consequence of the aggressor's activity. Today the Ustashas 
used 120-mm mortars to fiercely pound the demarcation lines and 
the residential areas in Bilo Polje, while the region of Bijelo 
was the target of multiple rocket launchers. The district of 
Blagaj was again exposed to artillery attacks perpetrated by the 
HVO and Croatian Army troops. 
  By accusing the [Bosnia-Herzegovina] Army of allegedly 
regrouping forces in the region of Blagaj -- as has been 
reported by the Croatian media -- the Ustashas are looking for 
an alibi for the daily shelling of this district and crimes 
committed against the civilian population, as well as for the 
attacks that they are obviously preparing to undertake against 
the free parts of the territory controlled by the 4th Corps 
forces. 

</TEXT>

