<H3> <TI>   Inter-Muslim Fighting Claims Casualties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401232694 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 2140 
GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401232694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Picture vs Picture" program] </F>
  [Excerpt] One of the most active Bosnia-Herzegovina 
battlefields is still Cazin Krajina. A correspondent of Serbian 
Banja Luka Television today reports about fierce internecine 
Muslim fighting. The news is that Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 
forces have launched a seemingly successful counteroffensive. 
  [Unidentified Banja Luka TV correspondent] Following fierce 
attacks by artillery and infantry, members of the 5th Corps of 
the so-called Bosnia-Herzegovina Army today inflicted this 
year's first defeat on the autonomist army. In fighting that 
continued all last night and this morning, Alija Izetbegovic's 
soldiers seized all strategically important sites around 
Pecigrad in the municipality of Cazin, shifting their lines by 1 
km toward Velika Kladusa, a town in which around 1,000 citizens 
of Pecigrad found shelter before the onslaught of Izetbegovic's 
killers today. 
  Internecine Muslim fighting also took place near Buzim 
today, 
where the combatants of the 5th Corps occupied the villages of 
Sestanovci and Marjanovici. Both sides have reported dozens of 
casualties. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

