<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Radio Programming Arranged for Serb Areas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401152694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1347 GMT 4 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, 4 Jan (TANJUG) -- A joint meeting of the 
radio stations of Banja Luka, Semberija and Majevica (Bijeljina) 
and Sarajevo -- the previous channel S, broadcast from Pale -- 
was held in Banja Luka today in connection with joint 
programming for a radio station in the republic of Srpska and 
the republic of Serb Krajina. 
  The joint programming will start on 17 January and implies 
joint broadcasts every working day between 0800 GMT and 1200 
GMT. Between these times each studio -- Banja Luka, Bijeljina, 
Knin and Sarajevo (Pale) -- will produce one hour of programs. 
The news and current affairs programs will be joint programs 
because the news -- at noon and 1500 -- will go out from the 
Sarajevo (Pale) studio, while the 1900 cast will be broadcast 
from Banja Luka. However, the Banja Luka studio will broadcast 
a news bulletin at 1500 on its second program, and it will have 
its own daily news program at 1600. 
  Joint weekend broadcasts begin on 14 January. They will 
begin at noon on Saturday. They will end at 0600 the following 
day, and the studios will be changed in accordance with an 
established timetable. 
  In addition to establishing common programs, principles amd 
ways of exchanging information were established, as were other 
forms of joint work in the unified RS and RSK radio. The 
meeting was also to have been attended by representatives of 
Serb Radio Knin, but they will be informed by letter of the 
agreement on joint programming. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

