<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Shelling Leaves 39 Dead, 200 Wounded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0401200394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0401200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the information of the republican 
Health Care Headquarters, 141,605 people have been killed and 
160,000 wounded in Bosnia-Herzegovina since the beginning of the 
war. In Sarajevo alone, 9,662 have been killed, while over 
56,000 were wounded. During the Christmas cease-fire, 106 
people were killed and 470 wounded. Thirty-nine people were 
killed and 200 wounded in Sarajevo. This is stated in the 
statement of the republican Health Care Headquarters. Death 
from starvation is threatening displaced persons and the rest of 
the population in Tesanj, Maglaj, Olovo, Gorazde, Mostar, Tuzla, 
and other cities. Therefore, it is necessary to secure powdered 
milk and other dairy products for these areas, as well as fresh, 
dried, and canned fruits, powdered eggs, meat products, and 
fresh and canned vegetables. 

</TEXT>

