<H3> <TI>   Ministry Says Year Ended With Budget Surplus </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0301190294 Prague CTK in English 1741 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0301190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Jan 3 (CTK) -- According to preliminary 
calculations, 1993 has come to a close with a slight budget 
surplus, Finance Ministry Spokesperson Ludmila Nutilova told CTK 
today. 
  She added that in a speech today, Finance Minister Ivan 
Kocarnik told ministry staff that few countries can boast of a 
budget surplus, and the Czech Republic is the only country 
undergoing transformation that has a surplus. The surplus, he 
said, is a sign of successful economic transformation, 
especially as the new tax system was instituted and enforced 
with no loans from the state. 

