<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grants for Minority Publications Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501200694 Prague CTK in English 1918 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Jan 5 (CTK) -- The Czech Government today 
granted almost 20 million crowns (680,000 USD) to support 
minority newspapers and magazines, a government spokesman 
announced. A similar grant in 1993 amounted to 18.5 million 
crowns. 
  The Polish, Ukrainian, German, Hungarian, Romany and Slovak 
minority press will benefit from the grant, Premier Vaclav Klaus 
said. The government also approved setting up 150 individual 
grants, to be created by 1996, for third world students wishing 
to take up university-level study, the government spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

