<H3> <TI>   Authorities Reportedly Seize Lexa's Passport </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501144394 Prague CTK in English 1314 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava Dec 31 (CTK) -- Slovak Foreign and 
Passport Police seized travel documents from Ivan Lexa, chairman 
of the Government Office, in connection with the accusation of 
defamation of the state and its representative, the pro-Meciar 
daily REPUBLIKA writes today. 
  Lexa is alleged to have cast doubt on the morals of the 
president and his professional capabilities in connection with 
his age. 
  According to the paper, Lexa considers it absurd that the 
Slovak criminal bodies deem his case to be so important that 
they made it impossible for him to travel abroad. He considers 
the unprecedented political trial to be comparable with those 
communist from the 1950's. 

</TEXT>

