<H3> <TI>   Komarno Citizens Seek To Dismiss Mayor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0401165394 Prague CTK in English 1613 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0401165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava Jan 4 (CTK) -- A group of citizens from 
the southern Slovak town of Komarno are seeking to dismiss 
Komarno Mayor Isztvan Pasztor, a leader of the Hungarian 
minority in southern Slovakia, Slovak Radio reported today. 
According to the radio, local discontent with the mayor's 
approach to solving daily problems of the town was the reason. 
Petitions demanding the mayor's resignation have been put up by 
civic initiatives at many places in the town and a public rally 
was called for Wednesday [5 January] in the headquarters of the 
Slovak cultural organisation Matica Slovenska. 
  Pasztor as chairman of the Council of the Association of 
Towns and Villages of the Zitny Island, is an initiator of a 
meeting of deputies and mayors from southern Slovakia scheduled 
for January 8 in Komarno to demand the establishment of a 
"region with special status" in southern Slovakia populated by a 
large Hungarian minority. Matica Slovenska has sharply 
condemned the meeting. 

</TEXT>

