<H3> <TI>   Residency Permit Fees for Slovaks Abolished </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0301150394 Prague CTK in English 1718 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0301150394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Jan 1 (CTK) -- As of today, the citizens of 
the Czech and Slovak Republics living in the other country will 
not pay administrative fees for issuing permanent residence 
permits. 
  The relevant note was handed to Vilem Holan, director of the 
Czech Foreign Ministry Slovak Department by counselor-envoy of 
the Slovak Embassy in Prague, Jozef Stank, on Thursday [30 
December]. The note reciprocates a note from the Czech Foreign 
Ministry of December 22. 
  The cancellation of the fees was initiated at the meeting 
between the Czech and Slovak presidents, Vaclav Havel and Michal 
Kovac, in Lany, Central Bohemia, on November 17. 

