<F P=101> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unemployment Rate `Rising'; Details Given </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0401190894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1728 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0401190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES 4/1/1994 -- The unemployment rate 
was of 10.2 on January 4, with the number of unemployed standing 
at 1,164,705, i.e. 8,000 more than on December 27, 1993. 2,000 
people were made redundant in the capital over December 27, 
1993-January 4, 1994, bringing the total number of Bucharest 
unemployed at 142,602. 
  Unemployed women outnumbered men. 1,065, 844 people were 
registered for unemployment benefits or subsistence allowances, 
of whom 422,673 are men and 623,171 women. 911,191 of the 
lay-offs are workers, 136,751 graduated high schools and 17,174 
higher schools. 428,636 people made redundant no longer 
received allowances as they no longer met the requirements of 
the law. 7,972 work places were available in the country and 
615 in the capital. 

</TEXT>

