<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plans for German Funding of Nuclear Plant Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0401210894 Prague CTK in English 2044 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0401210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava Jan 4 (CTK) -- The conditions for 
partial German funding of the construction of the nuclear power 
plant in Mochovce, West Slovakia, are to be specified in 
January, Slovak Vice-Premier for Economy Sergej Kozlik announced 
today. Kozlik took part in negotiations today with the German 
ambassador to Slovakia, Heike Zenker, on the completion of 
construction work in Mochovce and its financing. The key 
issues, in his opinion, concern the repayment of German loans 
through supplies of nuclear energy to Germany and the closing of 
the nuclear power plant in Jaslovske Bohunice, West Slovakia, on 
which the realization of the project is conditional. Kozlik 
said that clear economic calculations are necessary if Slovakia 
is to prove she can be depended on to repay her loans. A total 
of 1.5 billion DEM [German marks] in foreign loans is to be 
provided for the construction of the nuclear power plant in 
Mochovce. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

