<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> FRY Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ethnic Albanians Protest Border Charges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501121994 Tirana ATA in English 1113 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, January 5 (ATA) -- Upon the initiative of 
a group of citizens in Presheva, signatures for a petition are 
being taken for the lifting of taxes in the border points in 
Presheva, between rump Yugoslavia and the former Republic of 
Macedonia. The application of taxes affects all citizens, 
especially Albanians, because the Albanians of Presheva have 
many family relations with the Albanians of Macedonia, who have 
unjustly been divided by artificial borders. Since the first of 
January 1994, the border authorities of rump Yugoslavia demand 
10 DM per person and 30 DM per vehicle before leaving them to 
pass the border. 

</TEXT>

