<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Reports $304-Million Trade Deficit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501153394 Paris AFP in English 1410 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ljubljana, Jan 5 (AFP) -- Slovenia suffered a trade 
deficit of 304 million dollars for the first 11 months of 1993 
due to a sharp drop in exports and a small rise in imports, the 
Economics Ministry announced on Wednesday. 
  Exports amounted to 5.5 billion dollars for the period, off 
10.9 percent from the same period in 1992, while imports were 
set at 5.8 billion dollars, up 3.9 percent. 
  Economic Relations Minister Davorin Kracun said that despite 
the trade deficit, Slovenia's foreign exchange reserves had 
increased by around 300 million dollars over the period, to 
almost 1.5 billion dollars at present. 

</TEXT>

