<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bakir Izetbegovic Implicated in General's Murder </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501134794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1231 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, 5 Jan (TANJUG) -- A special unit of the 
Muslim Army commanded by Bakir Izetbegovic, son of Alija 
Izetbegovic, is responsible for the murder of Jusuf Juka 
Prazina, VJESNIK daily of Zagreb writes today. Citing 
well-informed sources, the Zagreb daily blames the operation on 
Delta, a five-member Muslim commando unit commanded by Ismet 
Bajramovic. 
  According to VJESNIK, three Palestinians and members of a 
pro-Syrian organization monitored Juka's movements for several 
weeks. One of them introduced himself as an arms dealer and took 
Juka to a parking lot near the Liege-Aachen road where he was 
killed. 
  "The liquidation of Juka Prazina was financed by the son of 
Alija Izetbegovic, Bakir, who left Sarajevo six months ago," 
VJESNIK says in its unsigned article. 
  According to the Zagreb daily, Bakir Izetbegovic "frequently 
travels between Brussels, Paris, Frankfurt, Baghdad, Tehran, and 
Ankara, using Pakistani and Iraqi passports." It is believed 
that Bakir Izetbegovic was in Belgium at the time of the 
assassination. 
  VJESNIK goes on to say that "Hasan Cengic, responsible for 
army logistics in the Sarajevo government, was directly involved 
in the assassination of Juka Prazina." 
  "Immediately after the assassination, those responsible left 
for Cairo and Khartoum via Brussels and Paris and Hasan Cengic 
left for Islamabad using a false Pakistani passport," VJESNIK 
writes. 

</TEXT>

