<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Convoy Prevented From Entering Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501163194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A UN High Commission for Refugees [UNHCR] convoy, 
which left Metkovic this morning for Zenica and Tuzla, was 
stopped at the Croatian Defense Council's [HVO] border 
checkpoint because of its failure to ask for a permit from the 
mixed commission and to fulfill other conditions required by the 
protocol on the organization of humanitarian operations, the 
Croat Republic of Herceg-Bosna government office for cooperation 
with the UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR], the European Union 
[EU], and international organizations says in its statement. 
  The convoy was instructed to return to Metkovic because the 
vehicles arrived at the border checkpoint without the necessary 
documents required by the regulations and agreements on 
humanitarian convoys and because the cargo was not checked at 
the point of departure. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

