<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Delivers Verdict on Ex-Politburo Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0401155094 Tirana ATA in English 1126 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> AU0401155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, December 31 (ATA) -- At the end of the 
penal case of the 10 former communist blockmen of the Party of 
Labour of Albania, accused of violation of the equality of 
citizens through the creation of privileges, the Tirana Court 
decided to arrest in the court hall the defendants Llambi 
Gegprifti, Lenka Cuko, and Hajredin Celiku. While seven other 
defendants, Pali Miska, Muho Asllani, Besnik Bekteshi, Qirjako 
Mihali, Vangjel Cerrava, Prokop Murra, and Foto Cami were 
punished with imprisonments terms respectively seven years and 
payment of 263,733 leks; six years and payment of 359,110 leks; 
eight years and payment of 402,753 leks; five years and payment 
of 193,340 leks; five years and payment of 474,906 leks; six 
years and payment of 313,118 leks. The jury also decided that 
all titles of honour and medals be from now on considered null 
and void for the defendants. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-49213 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu001__a94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-001-A </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  6 January 1994 </DATE1>

