<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Protests Border Shootings by Serbians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501142794 Tirana ATA in English 0905 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 5 (ATA) -- [words indistinct] On 
January 3, 1994, at 1030 hrs, in the border sign D14/18, in 
Zapod of Kukes, the Yugoslav border soldiers killed the Albanian 
citizen Ramadan Ibrahim Mustafa, 25 years, who was 5.5 meters in 
the Yugoslav territory. They opened fire against Ramadan at a 
15 meter distance causing him five wounds. 
  On the same day, at 1500, in the border zone of Tropoje, 
Serbian border forces opened fire from the Yugoslav territory 
wounding seriously in the Albanian zone the Albanian Citizen 
Hamid Ram Sallaku, 20 years. 
  These grave criminal acts, encouraged by vile anti-Albanian 
aims of Serbian chauvinists, are made in the course of similar 
acts in the past. In the incidents occurring in the border of 
Albania with Serbia and Montenegro, all the wounded and killed 
have been Albanians, none of them has been Serbian. With the 
last two victims, the number of those killed since the beginning 
of 1993 becomes 21. Such criminal acts are part of the strategy 
of tension and war that Milosevic is following, thus stirring up 
situations with unprecedented consequences in the region. 
  The Albanian Foreign Ministry forcefully protests against 
these incidents, which should be put an end immediately. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-49214 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu004__a94001" </HT>


