<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhelev Meets With Party, Public Representatives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0601180994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0601180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 6 January President Zhelyu Zhelev met 
representatives of the Bulgarian Social Democratic and Green 
Parties. The economic situation in the country, problems with 
structural and agrarian reforms, and the alarming growth in 
unemployment were discussed. Also discussed were issues of 
international importance, including the situation in Yugoslavia 
in particular and in the Balkans in general. 
  After the meeting Stefan Radoslavov, chief secretary of the 
Bulgarian Social Democratic Party, expressed satisfaction with 
the rather similar positions on various issues that were noted. 
  On behalf of the Green Party, Vladimir Sotirov conveyed to 
the president a charter on national unity worked out by Green 
Party experts. 
  President Zhelev also met representatives of the Union of 
Thracian Associations, Internal Macedonian Revolutionary 
Organization-Union of Macedonian Associations, the Initiative 
Committee on Protecting the Rights of Bulgarian Refugees, and 
the Green Party. They demanded that the president utilize his 
influence on the parliament and the cabinet and facilitate the 
solution of the problems of the refugees of the Aegean and 
Thracian Macedonia and the issue of compensating those refugees. 
A petition on this matter was submitted by the four 
organizations on 6 November 1993 to the parliament, and they 
expect a more rapid solution of the issue. 

</TEXT>

