<H3> <TI>   Five UN French Peacekeepers Wounded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0601184494 Paris AFP in English 1813 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0601184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo, Jan 6 (AFP) -- Five French soldiers 
in the United Nations Protection Force (UNPROFOR) were wounded 
on Thursday at Sarajevo airport, UNPROFOR Guy de Battista said 
here. 
  Two non-commissioned officers were seriously hurt, and 
underwent emergency operations but they would survive, and would 
be evacuated to France Friday, de Battista said. [passage 
omitted] 
  French forces have lost 18 killed and more than 260 wounded, 
a third of them seriously, since the UN intervention began in 
April 1992. Half of the casualties have been caused by 
fighting. [passage omitted] 

