<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic-Tudjman Talks Open in Bonn </TI></H3>
<H4>   Talks Follow `Old Pattern' </H4>
<F P=102> LD0901231394 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 2250 
GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0901231394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] We have just received the latest report from 
Bonn. Jozo Curic has the latest news. 
  [Curic] The second round of talks between Presidents Tudjman 
and Izetbegovic ended several minutes ago. The talks were 
initiated by the Croats, and I have learned from well-informed 
sources that the talks followed the old pattern. The Muslims 
accept Croatian peace and cooperation proposals in general but 
reject individual specific elements. Presidents Izetbegovic and 
Tudjman will meet briefly tomorrow morning and this will be 
followed by a plenary meeting. [passage omitted] 

