<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders on NATO, `Euro-Carpathian Region' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701155594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
0500 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0701155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During a news conference held yesterday, Mr. 
Nicolae Manolescu, chairman of the Civic Alliance Party [PAC], 
announced that representatives of the parties that are members 
of the Democratic Convention of Romania [CDR] will meet with 
Romania's President Ion Iliescu on Tuesday, 11 January. 
  During the news conference held yesterday by the leaders of 
the Democratic Party-National Salvation Front [PD-FSN], Messrs. 
Petre Roman and Adrian Severin expressed their worry over the 
possibility that Romania might not be among the countries that 
would be integrated into NATO first. Romania's integration into 
that body would both ensure national security and represent our 
country's acknowledgment as a part of the free world, the PD-FSN 
representatives said. 
  The vice chairman of the National Romanian Unity Party 
[PUNR], Mr. Ion Gavra, announced yesterday that his party had 
requested that the suggestions included in its anticrisis 
program should be implemented by the government within a 
so-called austerity program that is to be presented in 
parliament at the beginning of February. 
  A communique released yesterday by the Greater Romania Party 
[PRM] announces that they learned with deep concern about the 
decisions taken by the Satu Mare and Maramures County Councils 
on their adherence to the so-called Euro-Carpathian region, an 
artificial structure that endangers Romania's security and 
integrity. The PRM demands that the illegal decisions of the 
two chairmen of the aforementioned county councils should 
immediately be annulled. 

</TEXT>

