<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TU Leaders Demand Coalition Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701174894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0701174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning the representatives of the main trade 
union confederations held a news conference, which was attended 
by Bogdan Hossu, chairman of Cartel Alfa, Miron Mitrea, the 
executive chairman of CNSLR [National Council of Romania's Free 
Trade Unions]-Fratia, and Marian Miclici, general secretary of 
the National trade Union Bloc [BNS]. During the news 
conference, Hossu announced that during yesterday's conference 
of the executive bodies of the three trade union confederations 
they agreed upon a program of action in the near future, as they 
all consider that the sole solution to the current economic and 
social problems is to go on a general strike. Therefore, on 28 
January, a one-hour warning general strike, on 4 February a 
one-day strike, and, beginning with 16 February, an open-ended 
general strike will begin, until all demands are met. Hossu 
added that he personally hopes that the labor conflict will be 
ended before 15 January. The precondition to this is that the 
government should also consider the demands forwarded by the 
trade unions, including the one requesting the establishment of 
a coalition government, in which case there will be no reasons 
to go on the planned strikes, which are actually not wanted by 
anyone, Hossu emphasized. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

