<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Deficit Grows in November </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601150794 Warsaw PAP in English 1423 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Jan. 6 -- The Polish trade deficit increased 
to 2,036 m [million] dollars after 11 months of 1993, according 
to a high ranking official of the National Bank of Poland (NBP). 
After 10 months the deficit amounted to only 1,949 m dollars. 
The same official told reporters here Thursday [6 January] that 
foreign exchange reserves of the bank at the end of November 
amounted to 3,840 m dollars. 

</TEXT>

