<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Podkrepa Plans Antigovernment National Strike </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0901180594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0901180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Podkrepa National Strike Committee held a 
meeting today at the headquarters of the Podkrepa Labor 
Confederation, which was attended by representatives of the 
strike committees of 15 federations and 21 regions throughout 
the country. 
  The participants adopted a draft decision, which notes that 
a 
strike situation exists in the country. The General Assembly 
proposes to the Podkrepa Executive and Federative Councils to 
complete the preparations for national strike activities by 1 
February. Those activities will be aimed, I quote, against the 
antihuman and antisocial policy of Professor Berov's government. 
  The draft decision will be submitted to the Podkrepa 
Federative Council, which is scheduled to meet on 16-17 January 
in Blagoevgrad. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

