<H3> <TI>   Baudys Denies Movement Away From Visegrad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701174094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1500 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Antonin Baudys today rejected 
speculation that the Czech Republic is setting itself apart from 
the Visegrad Group. With regard to his canceled trip to Warsaw, 
Baudys said that his deputy, Jiri Pospisil, is well qualified to 
fully cover for him. 
  According to Minister Baudys, the envisaged visit by 
President Bill Clinton is an exceptional event. However, the 
minister noted that the Army is not preparing any extraordinary 
measures or alert. The only measure is that the military police 
will cooperate with the municipal police, the Interior Ministry, 
and other bodies, in order to protect public order. 

</TEXT>

