<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Banja Luka Serbs Issue Anti-Karadzic Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701204094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0701204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have to broker a truce with our neighbors and 
embark on a revival of the economy and the restoration of our 
cities. We also demand the proclamation of the autonomy of the 
Banja Luka region and the setting of democratic elections for 
the assembly and government of the Krajina. This is stated in 
the statement released by the Banja Luka Regional Council of the 
Serbian People's Front just before the New Year holidays. 
  We were (?pushed) into battle in order to ensure that all 
Serbs live in one state, but 100,000 of us were killed in the 
process. In addition to this, we are threatened by an 
international slaughter. Our Krajina can live and prosper 
without Pale. That is why we demand that normal people be 
allowed to conduct political life. They are lying when they say 
that the corridor means life for our children, because our 
children have a greater need for living fathers. Corridors will 
abound in peacetime, and they will be as wide as our hearts. 
However, when we say all this, we are openly arrested and 
persecuted by Karadzic's henchmen. This is stated in the 
statement issued by the Banja Luka Regional Council of the 
Serbian People's Front. 

</TEXT>

