  [Text] Sarajevo, 10 Jan (TANJUG) -- The National Assembly 
of the Srpska republic resumed in Pale just before 1100 today. 
Deputies are considering drafts of, and proposals for, 
legislation affecting the economy. 
  The final item on the agenda is a debate on the peace talks 
in Geneva and Brussels. Dr. Radovan Karadzic, president of the 
Srpska republic, will make introductory remarks on this topic. 

