<H3> <TI>   Factional Muslim Fighting in Cazin Krajina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001140394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1311 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Petrovac, 10 Jan (TANJUG) -- Fierce clashes in Cazin 
Krajina continued last night and today between members of the 
Muslim Army loyal to Izetbegovic and supporters of Fikret Abdic, 
local Muslim sources have announced. 
  The same sources add that the forces of the [pro-Abdic] 
autonomous province of western Bosnia [APZB], using all 
available means, have taken the village of Trzac [northwest of 
Cazin] and inflicted great losses on the army loyal to the 
Sarajevo authorities. 
  Izetbegovic's forces, using infantry and artillery weapons, 
are trying to break through the demarcation lines and infiltrate 
inside the APZB, but are not succeeding. The [pro-Abdic] 
Western Bosnian news agency, ZBIA, reports that both sides have 
suffered a large number of dead and injured. 

</TEXT>

