  [Excerpts] This is Ivica Saric reporting for Croatian radio 
from Vitez [passage omitted] 
  The HVO [Croatian Defense Council] units have the initiative 
now and they are trying to retake control of the Vitez-Busovaca 
road. Fierce hand-to-hand combat is still going on. Muslim 
artillery attacks are continuing. More than 100 shells landed 
on Vitez by 1600 and over 200 shells of various caliber were 
fired on the defense lines. Five elderly people and one child 
were killed and 35 civilians were wounded, including many 
children. The defenders have also suffered casualties in heavy 
fighting. [passage omitted] 
  As I am filing this report, dozens of shells are falling on 
Vitez and according to military sources, the Muslim army is 
bringing in fresh units and military equipment from Zenica so 
that new, even stronger, aggressor attacks are expected during 
the night or morning on this part of the front in the Lasva 
river valley. 

