<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thousands of Croats `Encircled' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901110094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0901110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At 0500, Muslims began a ferocious combined infantry 
and artillery attack and took the northeast approaches to Vitez 
and the village of Buhine Kuce, thus cutting off the 
Vitez-Busovaca road. Eight thousand civilians and 7,500 Croat 
refugees are encircled in Busovaca. Our correspondent in Vitez 
reports that fears are increasing of a tragedy on the scale of 
Krizancevo Selo as the lives of 50-60 civilians from Buhine Kuce 
are in danger. 
  We have just received a report from the Vitez operational 
zone command that troops of the British UN battalion are 
patrolling the Vitez-Busovaca road, extending their protection 
to civilians fleeing from Buhine Kuce and transporting them to 
Vitez. Six people have been taken care of so far, and a British 
liaison officer said that members of their tank units, located 
by the road, saw the bodies of two civilians. 
  By 0800, three people were killed and 15 injured in the 
ongoing artillery attack on the center of Vitez. The HVO's 
[Croatian Defense Council] 111th Zepce Brigade reported that 
Muslims were also launching artillery attacks on Zepce and that 
many have been wounded there as well. 
  According to the latest information, Muslims are attacking 
the Kuber area near Vitez from the direction of Zenica, while 
the HVO reports that the Muslim breakthrough in the Buhine Kuce 
area has been halted. 

</TEXT>

