<H3> <TI>   UN Troops Exhume Mass Grave </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701211894 Paris AFP in English 2053 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0701211894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, Jan 7 (AFP) -- British UN troops have 
exhumed a mass grave containing the bodies of 27 Croats killed 
by Bosnian Government troops in a village near the central 
Bosnian town of Vitez, a UN spokesmans said Friday. 
  Bosnian Croats forces (HVO) have accused the 
Moslem-dominated 
government army of massacring some 50 civilians in an attack on 
the village of Dubravica on December 22 and have demanded an 
international inquiry. 
  British forces in the area began a search for graves and on 
Thursday exhumed 27 bodies from a trench in the presence of UN 
military and European Community observers, but said they had no 
concrete evidence of a massacre. 
  Lindsey French, a spokeswoman for the British battalion 
contacted in Split, said the bodies were all dressed in HVO 
uniforms all carried "wounds received in a battle." 
  "We have no indication of any form of massacre," she said. 

</TEXT>

