<H3> <TI>   Serbs Prevent Electricity Repairs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1001100494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1001100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ten megawatts of electricity are reaching Sarajevo 
today. This is enough only for basic humanitarian needs. The 
Serbian side still has not given its approval for beginning 
repairs on the Reljevo-[name indistinct] long distance 
transmission line, so it is uncertain when citizens will be 
supplied with electricity. 
  The waterworks information service informs that they are 
still having problems and that the amount of water supplied to 
the city is still inadequate. The pumping system [words 
indistinct]. Nevertheless, the supply of water to Sarajevo is 
improving. Water is being supplied every day or every other 
day. No water is coming in from the Jahorina springs and there 
is no possibility of alternately supplying water in a part of 
the supply zone of (?Hamdina Carina). The Pivara spring is 
operational and only the water from this spring is chlorinated. 
  Today the Sarajevo bakery will supply bread to the majority 
of communes in the city and to all priority consumers. 
Tomorrow's production is uncertain owing to lack of [words 
indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

