<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ethnic Hungarians Kept From Attending Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801150294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1400 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] In Slovakia, police prevented representatives 
from Districts Lucenec and Filakovo from getting to the meeting 
of Zitny Ostrov localities. [passage omitted] First policemen 
asked for documents certifying the payment of road tax, which is 
levied on weekends. After these documents were presented, they 
took away vehicle registration documents without giving any 
reason. They only told the protesting passengers that whatever 
they did, the buses could not leave the territory of the Slovak 
district. 

</TEXT>

