<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic-Tudjman Talks Open in Bonn </TI></H3>
<H4>   Germany's Kinkel Comments </H4>
<F P=102> LD0901182994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1752 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0901182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Germany's Foreign Minister 
Klaus Kinkel this evening welcomed the presidents of Bosnia and 
Croatia, Alija Izetbegovic and Franjo Tudjman, at Petersberg 
near Bonn. [passage omitted] 
  Immediately after the welcoming ceremony in the marble hall 
of the government's guest house, the presidents, the mediators, 
and Kinkel withdrew to the conference hall. Kinkel intends to 
leave the scene of the negotiations following brief preliminary 
talks. 
  Kinkel previously disclosed that the talks are taking place 
at the initiative of himself and his French counterpart Alain 
Juppe. Kinkel voiced the hope that there would be "steps 
forward" at the talks. He added that he would leave this 
evening for advance talks prior to the NATO summit beginning in 
Brussels tomorrow. He wished the Bosnian-Croatian negotiations 
a "good outcome." The public will be advised of developments in 
the talks as soon as this is "worthwhile." 

</TEXT>

