<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhelev Not To Seek Second Term </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0901175894 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0901175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] On 9 January, President Zhelyu Zhelev answered 
questions put forth by listeners of Khorizont radio. 
  I hope that by the end of my mandate, in approximately three 
years, the basic reforms will have been implemented in Bulgaria. 
Afterward, other people can continue, the president said, 
stressing that he will not seek a second term as a president. 
[passage omitted] 
  If any political force tries to hinder settling the foreign 
debt issue, it would be committing an act of national treason, 
the president said. He noted that in his upcoming address to 
the National Assembly, he will stress the necessity of rapidly 
adopting the budget and the bills that are extremely necessary 
for foreign debt negotiations and the IMF agreement. 
  According to the president, it is very important to achieve 
a 
consensus in the parliament on measures needed by the country. 
He would like to see the meeting between Filip Dimitrov and 
Zhan Videnov contribute to this end. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

