<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Wants NATO To Help Lift Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901194194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0901194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The aggression against the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, an internationally recognized country and UN 
member, has been going on for as long as 21 months. The 
aggression was planned and is being carried out by Serbia and 
Montenegro. Their fascists have so far managed to produce 
evidence that civil war is now at issue here, a letter sent by 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Defense Hamdija Hadzihasanovic to the defense 
ministers of NATO member-countries said. 
  All that the international community is doing is delivering 
humanitarian aid, which helps us survive--until we are killed by 
the aggressor's shells and snipers, though. The belief that the 
war can be contained within the borders of Bosnia-Herzegovina is 
wrong. 
  We shall never give up. We are numerous enough and we are 
determinted to fight to the end. Death is not painful. 
Humiliation is painful. To us the word life implies freedom and 
justice, the Bosnia-Herzegovina defense minister writes in his 
letter. 
  Milosevic can only be stopped by force. Europe and the world 
have this kind of force, Hadzihasanovic writes in his letter to 
the the Defense Ministers 16 NATO member-countries, demanding 
their help in lifting the embargo on importing arms to 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

