<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zieleniec Distances NATO From Visegrad Basis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0601202194 Prague CTK in English 1840 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0601202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Jan 6 (CTK) -- The Czech Republic would like 
to take the question of its integration with NATO out of the 
"excessively structuralised and insitutionalised Visegrad 
process, Czech Foreign Minister Josef Zieleniec told journalists 
today. [no closing quotation mark as received] 
  At the same time Zieleniec stressed that there were many 
questions of mutual interest in the Central European region 
which should be solved within the Visegrad Four group (the Czech 
Republic, Slovakia, Poland, Hungary). These were the questions 
directly connected with life in the area, economic cooperation 
and cooperation in the building of the region's infrastructure 
as well as "several political problems," he said. 
  On the other hand, however, the philosophy of the 
transformation of Czech society is characterised by "relying on 
its own strength," Zieleniec said. He said he did not consider 
it appropriate to unnecessarily emphasise the exclusiveness of 
the Visegrad group. The exclusion of other countries from the 
European integration processes was not in the interests of Czech 
foreign policy, he said. 

</TEXT>

