<H3> <TI>   `Anarchists' Plan Anti-Clinton Protest 11 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701195494 Prague CTK in English 1655 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0701195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Jan 7 (CTK) -- An assembly to protest U.S. 
President Bill Clinton's upcoming visit to Prague is being 
planned by local anarchists for January 11 on Old Town Square, 
said Jakub Polak, editor-in-chief of the magazine A-KONTRA, at a 
press conference of the Left Alternative and the Czechoslovak 
Anarchist Association today. 
  In addition to the assembly, Polak said, a series of other 
demonstrations, manifestations and protests are being prepared. 
Polak would not specify any times or locations "so they will not 
be prevented." 
  Polak called Clinton the representative of a country "that 
is 
not qualified to be a parliament of human rights and that does 
not have the right to talk about peace." The President himself 
"awakens false hopes" and his policies "postpone necessary 
changes," Polak said. 
  Prague Police Spokesman Petr Link told CTK today that the 
police had not been notified of any demonstrations in connection 
with Clinton's visit. 

