<F P=103> LD0701120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 7 Jan -- President Lech Walesa today 
received Ambassador Madeleine Albright, President Bill Clinton's 
special envoy. Her mission is connected with the program of 
"Partnership for Peace" put forward by the United States. 
  Underscoring U.S. merits in building democracy in Europe, 
President Walesa said that, in his view as a former soldier, one 
has to use favorable moments and apply a "lead forward tactic." 
"I am of the opinion that there is a chance today for a leap 
ahead in Europe," the president said. He added that, while 
recognizing U.S. responsibility for the world, "we do not want 
to hinder great ideas, but we want to present our stand." 
  Among members of the U.S. delegation is General John 
Shalikashvili, head of the Joint Chiefs of Staff of the U.S. 
armed forces. 

