<H3> <TI>   Hofbauer Declines Comment on RFE Cancellation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701064394 Prague CTK in English 2111 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0701064394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava Jan 5 (CTK) -- Minister of Transport, 
Communications and Public Works Roman Hofbauer today declined to 
comment on whether Slovakia would insist on Radio Free Europe 
[RFE] ending its broadcasts January 31. 
  Last month Hofbauer decided to cancel a 1990 agreement 
between RFE and Czechoslovakia which granted the station the 
right to broadcast on a medium wavelength until 1996. As a 
legal successor to Czechoslovakia, the Slovak Republic is bound 
by the agreement. 
  Asked for a response to a U.S. State Department spokesman 
who 
said America hoped Slovakia would reverse its decision, Hofbauer 
said he was unaware of any such statement. 
  Talks between Slovakia and RFE on continuing broadcasts, 
possibly on a shortwave frequency, are scheduled for January 20. 

</TEXT>

