<H3> <TI>   Kovac Cites `Irresponsible' Ethnic Politicians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0801183694 Prague CTK in English 1458 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0801183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava Jan 7 (CTK) -- Slovak President Michal 
Kovac, in his statement on the problem of ethnic minorities in 
Slovakia published in the independent daily SME today, stressed 
that it was in the interest of Slovaks, ethnic Hungarians and 
other nationalities and ethnic groups in Slovakia to seek to 
prevent irresponsible politicians from southern Slovakia from 
artificially creating a conflict situation. 
  Kovac's statement calls for dialogue and rejects the 
expressions of nationalism that appeared in a Hungarian-language 
daily on the eve of a meeting of representatives of the 
Hungarian minority in Komarno convened by the Association of 
Towns and Villages of Zitny Island. 
  Although Kovac resolutely rejected as unconstitutional a 
proposal to create a special province in southern Slovakia, at 
the same time he supported as justified demand that the new 
territorial administrative division of Slovakia not discriminate 
against the Hungarian minority. 

</TEXT>

