<F P=100> Yugoslavia </F>
<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Examines Albanian Education Possibilities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0701182694 Tirana ATA in English 1120 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0701182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 7 (ATA) -- The leading council of 
the Party for Democratic Prosperity [PPD] in Macedonia, the 
biggest party of the Albanians in this former Yugoslav Republic, 
examined in one of its meetings the problem of the education of 
the Albanians in Macedonia. It asked for new possibilities for 
their education, because the number of the Albanians enrolled in 
schools in Macedonia is small. 
  The juridical commission of this party is working to prepare 
a draft law for the creation of private higher schools to be 
presented to the Macedonian parliament. There is hope that this 
parliament may help solve the problem of education in the 
Albanian language in Macedonia. 

</TEXT>

