<F P=100> Yugoslavia </F>
<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Confiscate Copies of Albanian Publication </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0901151294 Tirana ATA in English 0915 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0901151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 9 (ATA) -- Macedonian police 
confiscated some 350 copies of the Albanian review JEHONA in the 
border crossing between Presheve and Kumanove. JEHONA is 
published by NOVA MAKEDONIA Printing Press in Skopje and is 
distributed in Kosova and other ethnically Albanian territories. 
The Macedonian police had confiscated some 350 copies of JEHONA 
three months ago. 

</TEXT>

